<br>
- You have to have Luclin on your account to do AA.<br>
<br>
- You have to be at least level 51.<br>
<br>
- When you decide to start earning them, hit <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> V</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> and a screen will pop up. There is a slider on the screen that sets how much of your XP gets diverted from leveling to AA. It can be 0 to 100% in 10% increments. The screen also shows all the abilities possible in each of the 3 'levels' of AA acheivement - General, Archtype, and Class.<br>
<br>
- Once you hit 51 you will have a 2nd XP bar below the current one. That shows how much you have earned towards your current AA point. It works just like your leveling XP bar, and gets filled by whatever proportion of your XP you set with the slider on the Alternate Advancement screen. Each point takes aproximately the same amount of XP as leveling from 51 to 52.<br>
<br>
- There are 3 sets of AA abilites available. :<br>
1)General - increases to basic ability scores/resists, run speed, regneration, and a couple other little things. Each level purchased in each of these costs 1 AA point. Everyone has the same General list available, and you can start earning these at level 51.<br>
2)Archtype - These abilities are dependant on your class (Melee,Priest,Caster), can't be earned until level 55, and can't be done until you have spent 6 points in General. The costs of these abilites are progressive (level 1 costs 2, level 2 costs 4 more [ total of 6 ], level 3 costs 6 more [ total 12 ]). This is the category where Mental Clarity rests.<br>
3)Class - each class has its own set of abilities (though there is a certain degree of overlap between classes). These come in 2 types - leveled abilites and single level abilities. The leveled abilites cost 3/6/9. The single level abilities have a one-time cost to provide a fixed benefit (things like 9 points to buy Mass Group Buff, 5? points to but Pet Discipline (/pet hold command)).To earn these abilites you must be level 59 and have spent at least 12 points in Archtype abilities. Some Class level abilites also require that you have a certain level in a specific Archtype ability before you can earn them (no mage abilites have such a requirement though).<br>
<br>
To find out what the specific abilities do, hit <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> V</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> and look through the lists. Some of the descriptions aren't quite correct, but they are close enough to give you a general idea. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showPrevMessage?topicID=117.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showNextMessage?topicID=117.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=117.topic&index=1><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.threadControl?topicID=117.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/unread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=117.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=117.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub102.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="themagicianstowerannouncements">Administration<option value="themagicianstowergeneral">General<option value="themagicianstowerfrm32">Class Balance<option value="themagicianstowerfrm45">User Interface<option value="themagicianstowerspells